
Some brief notes about Ethnomethodological concepts.

Background expectancies - the frame against which we render visible the locally situated meanings. They are the expectations that shape our reactions to sequences of action. 
These are locally situated. Thee

Accounts - There always exists a gap between the formalized and accounted-for representation of the world and "ordinary immortal society." Accounts, and the production of accounts, is a big chunk of the kinds of work we as academics, scientists and humanists alike, find ourselves doing. My writing these words is part of that accounting-work. Much of ethnomethodological studies of sicence are observing the production of accounts and the  work oriented around scientific "contexts of accountability" (not structures of accountability). The work in the pulsar paper of making the celestial object globally recognized as a "pulsar"

So there are two kinds of innovation. 